snippet.textDisplay: Hi everyone I’m 8 and I just wanted to tell u a little amazing something that I had happened in 2019 January, I’m from Albany and we went to Perth to watch the BBL , thunder vs scorchers ,yes scorchers didn’t win but that’s not what I’m talking about ,we mite of not won but I was just happy about going there ,so I’m a Woolworths cricket blast player and I’m autistic and I was so happy when I heard I had a chance to meet one of the players out on the field! , I was so excited,so there I was sitting in the crowd wait for when I could get my hat signed,but I happily watched the cricket and laughed at what the DJ was doing , also I was so happy to have my dads best friend that feels like my uncle and I’m girl btw . Once it was time for us to go meet with some people that took us out on the field I made friends with other kids too! We went in a lift and we got there and it was the biggest firework show ever in Optus yet! And guess who walked past us?ADAM GILCHRIST! My brother and my dad have met him before an d he remembered us! The lady numbered us I was number 1 my brother was number 2 but I could not see him so when the players ran out on the Field I was so nervous 😬 but excited 😊 too And the player walked up to me OMG I thought 💭, he said hi there I’m Mitch an u are , i gulped and said tess he gave me the hat and walked off smiling I never wanted that moment to end ! I wish I could of gave him a BIG hug and we could of talked longer ,I walked back to my mum and dad and I asked them who it was , I could not believe it the captain MITCHELL MARSH! I said now he and liveingstone are my fav players

Maybe bring in Hazelwood in place of Richardson.

Looking forward to the next match.
